## Alert & Confirmation Patterns

### SweetAlert2 Integration
**ALWAYS use SweetAlert2** for all alert dialogs, confirmations, and notifications. Never use native JavaScript `alert()`, `confirm()`, or `prompt()`.

**Import Pattern:**
```typescript
import Swal from 'sweetalert2';
```

**Standard Confirmation Dialog:**
```typescript
Swal.fire({
  title: 'Delete Item',
  text: `Are you sure you want to delete "${item.name}"?`,
  icon: 'warning',
  showCancelButton: true,
  confirmButtonColor: '#d33',
  cancelButtonColor: '#3085d6',
  confirmButtonText: 'Yes, delete it!',
  cancelButtonText: 'Cancel'
}).then((result) => {
  if (result.isConfirmed) {
    // Perform action
  }
});
```

**Success Notification:**
```typescript
Swal.fire({
  title: 'Success!',
  text: 'Operation completed successfully.',
  icon: 'success',
  confirmButtonColor: '#3085d6'
});
```

**Error Alert:**
```typescript
Swal.fire({
  title: 'Error!',
  text: 'Something went wrong.',
  icon: 'error',
  confirmButtonColor: '#d33'
});
```

### Color Standards for SweetAlert2
- **Confirm/Delete Button**: `#d33` (red for destructive actions)
- **Cancel/Default Button**: `#3085d6` (blue matching app theme)
- **Success Button**: `#3085d6` (blue for positive actions)

